<hl>
<seg id=1> 25 Storied High-rise in Detroit Leveled Down in 30 Seconds </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Agence Francaise de Press, Detroit) - 107 years old Hardeson Building became a debris within 30 seconds the day before yesterday. </seg>
<seg id=3> This reinforced steel bar framed building was 25 storied tall. It was one of the tallest buildings destroyed by directional blast of plastic explosive. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Hardeson Building was one of the largest retail shops in the world, and also the landmark of Detroit. </seg>
<seg id=5> In the blast sound of 1215 kilograms of plastic explosive, it finally became 3.06 million kilograms of debris. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> At 5:45 local time in that afternoon, a series of inward explosive began in Hardeson Building, dense and strong dust became huge fog swallowed all the people around the site. </seg>
<seg id=7> A citizen said: "I have never thought that I will be blackened all over by the dust." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> When the building was collapsing, some spectators cheered, but others were wiping their tears, as they would never see this familiar building again. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> In its heyday of 1950s, about 100,000 people go to Hardeson building for shopping everyday. </seg>
<seg id=10> At that time, some famous movie stars like Jiabao and Parker etc also came here. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=11> Detroit mayor Elche indicated to the public that: "The authority will give the opportunity of start the igniter to the public to collect 150,000 US dollars for charity donation." </seg>
<seg id=12> But because Hardeson building was Detroit's glory in former days, no one would like to start the igniter to destroy this building by himself. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=13> A man who stood for protection of this building said: "This is a sad thing." </seg>
</p>
